_meanings:
{@--1@} To be,
become; {#kaTamevaM BavennAma; asyAH#} 
{#kimaBavat#} <ls>Māl. 9. 29</ls> ‘what has become
her fate,’ ‘what has become of her’;
<ls>U. 3. 27</ls>; {#yadBAvi tadBavatu#} <ls>U. 3</ls> ‘come
what may’; so {#duHKito Bavati, hfzwo#} 
{#Bavati#} &c.

{@--2@} To be born or produced;
{#yadapatyaM BavedasyAM#} <ls>Ms. 9. 127</ls>;  
{#BAgyakrameRa hi DanAni BavaMti yAMti#} <ls>Mk. 1. 13.</ls>

{@--4@} To happen, take place, occur;
{#nAtatAyivaDe dozo haMturBavati kaScana#}  
<ls>Ms. 8. 381</ls>; {#yadi saMSayo Bavet#} &c.

{@--5@} To live,
exist; {#aBUdaBUtapUrvaH… rAjA#} 
{#ciMtAmaRirnAma#} <ls>Vās.</ls>; {#aBUnnfpo vibuDasaKaH paraMtapaH#}
<ls>Bk. 1. 1.</ls>

{@--6@} To be alive or living,
breathe; {#tvamidAnIM na Bavizyasi#} <ls>Ś. 6</ls>; 

{#AH cArudattahataka ayaM na Bavasi#} <ls>Mk. 4</ls>;
{#durAtman prahara nanvayaM na Bavasi#} <ls>Māl. 5</ls>
(‘thou art a dead man’, thou shalt
breathe no longer); <ls>Bg. 11. 32.</ls>

{@--7@}
To remain or be in any state or 
condition, fare; {#BavAn sTale kaTaM Bavizyati#}
<ls>Pt. 2.</ls>

{@--11@} To lead or tend to,
conduce to, bring about (with
<ab>dat.</ab>); {#vAtAya kapilA vidyut… pItA#}
{#Bavati sasyAya durBikzAya sitA Bavet#} <ls>Mbh.</ls>;
{#suKAya tajjanmadinaM baBUva#} <ls>Ku. 1. 23</ls>;
{#saMsmftirBava BavatyaBavAya#} <ls>Ki. 18. 27</ls>; {#na#}
{#tasyA rucaye baBUva#} <ls>R. 6. 44.</ls>

{@--12@} To be
on the side of, assist; {#devA arjunato'#} 
{#Bavan#}

{@--13@} To belong or pertain to
(often expressed by ‘have’); {#tasya#}
{#ha SataM jAyA baBUvuH#} <ls>Ait. Br.</ls>;  
<ls>Ms. 6. 39.</ls>

{@--14@} To be engaged in, be 
occupied (with <ab>loc.</ab>); {#caraRakzAlane kfzRo#}
{#brAhmaRAnAM svayaM hyaBUt#} <ls>Mb.</ls>

{@--16@} <ab>Ved.</ab>
To be prosperous, succeed. Used
with a preceding noun or adjective
{#BU#} serves to form verbs in the sense
of ‘becoming what it previously is
not’ or ‘becoming’ in general;  
{#SvetIBU#} to become white; {#kfzRIBU#} to
become black; {#payoDarIBUta#} 
‘becoming or serving the purpose of teats’;
so {#kzapaRIBU#} to be or become a 
mendicant; {#praRiDIBU#} to act the spy;  
{#ArdrIBU#} to melt; {#BasmIBU#} to be reduced
to ashes; {#vizayIBU#} to form the 
subject of; so {#ekamatIBU; taruRIBU#} &c. &c.
{%Note%}--The senses of {#BU#} may be 
variously modified according to the 
adverbs with which it is connected;
{%<ab>e. g.</ab>%} {#punarBU#} to marry again; {#a virBU#} to
appear, arise, to be evident or clear;
see {#Avis; tiroBU#} to disappear; {#prAdurBU#}
to arise, be visible, appear; {#agreBU#} to be
in front, take the lead; {#aMtarBU#} to be
absorbed or included;  
{#ojasyaMtarBavaMtyanye#} <ls>K. P. 8</ls>; {#dozABU#} to grow 
evening or dusk-time; {#anyaTA BU#} to be
otherwise, be changed; {#na me#} 
{#vacanamanyaTA Bavitumarhati#} <ls>Ś. 4</ls>; {#puro BU#} to
come forward, stand forth; {#miTyA BU#}
to turn out false; {#vfTA BU#} to become
useless &c. &c.

{@--4@} To
foster, cherish, support, preserve,
enliven; {#punaH sfjati varzARi BagavAn#} 
{#BAvayanprajAH#} <ls>Mb.</ls>; {#devAn BAvayatAnena te#}
{#devA BAvayaMtu vaH . parasparaM BAvayaMtaH SreyaH#}
{#paramavApsyaTa#} <ls>Bg. 3. 11</ls>; <ls>Bk. 16. 27.</ls>

{@--6@} To look upon,
consider or regard as; {#arTamanarTaM#} 
{#BAvaya nityaM#} <ls>Moha M. 2.</ls>
